&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;aCommerce The Next Gen 2026&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you ready to kick-start your career in the exciting world of e-commerce?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our &lt;strong&gt;Internship Program 2026&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is open to students from all backgrounds who are eager to gain hands-on experience in the dynamic and ever-evolving e-commerce industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Opening Internship Roles:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Performance Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intern - Academy Program
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Academy Program Intern will support the aCommerce Academy Team with the coordination and logistics of learning programs, including organizing training sessions, managing content, and preparing reports. This is an opportunity for a detail-oriented, collaborative individual, proficient in Thai and English, to gain hands-on experience in corporate learning and development within a supportive e-commerce environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intern - Document AI Processor
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Document AI &amp;amp; RPA Development Intern is involved in the end-to-end lifecycle of intelligent automation, focusing on teaching AI to &quot;read&quot; and process documents. Key responsibilities include data labeling for AI model training and assisting in the design, building, and testing of RPA workflows to automate internal use cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intern - Product Communication
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As a Product Communication Intern at aCommerce, you will join a passionate team to create diverse content including product guides, social media posts, and email campaigns. You will collaborate across departments to support product launches and integrate customer feedback into development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Account Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intern - Key Account Management (Thailand)
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Key Account Management Intern is support the marketing team in the fast-paced e-commerce industry, with responsibilities covering market research, content creation, influencer campaign coordination, and administrative support. The role requires strong organizational skills, basic Excel proficiency, and a high interest in social media trends and pop culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marketing Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intern - Communication Planning &amp;amp; Strategy
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This intern will primarily support the KOL&amp;amp;Affiliate lifecycle by sourcing and managing the talent pool, coordinating relationships, and overseeing execution. Key responsibilities also include managing KOL planning, payment processes, and providing essential data and reporting support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intern - Social Commerce (Indonesia)&lt;br&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This Social Commerce Intern is responsible for coordinating daily live streams, creating and editing engaging short-form video content, and performing on-camera product demonstrations. The ideal candidate will be confident, charismatic, possess basic to intermediate video editing skills, and have a strong understanding of current social media and live commerce trends to drive sales and community engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intern - Marketing Key Account Management
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Marketing Key Account Management Intern supports the Key Account team by managing client accounts, tracking campaign performance metrics (KPIs, ROAS), and coordinating internal marketing execution across four key areas: Client &amp;amp; Account Support, Performance &amp;amp; Data Tracking, Campaign Execution Support, and Administrative Coordination&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Communication Strategy:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement communication plans tailored to clients&#39; e-commerce goals and target audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay abreast of e-commerce industry trends, technological advancements, and competitor strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with cross-functional teams to ensure consistent messaging and branding across various e-commerce channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Short Video Production:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conceptualize, script, and&amp;nbsp; coordinate to produce short videos that showcase our clients&#39; products and services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the creative team to ensure the video content is aligned with the client&#39;s brand and product offerings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize videos for various e-commerce platforms, ensuring they drive engagement and conversions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Live Streaming Marketing:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and coordinate to execute live streaming campaigns on e-commerce platforms and social platforms to engage with our client&#39;s target audiences in real-time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor live streams and media plan (if any) to optimize product visibility and conversion rates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze live streaming performance data and adjust strategies for maximum ROI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Influencer and Affiliate Management:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage influencer and affiliate marketing programs tailored to drive awareness, traffic, and sales for our e-commerce clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and establish relationships with influential figures in e-commerce platforms and social platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with influencer and affiliate partners to promote our clients&#39; campaigns effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reports&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and report weekly or monthly on all activities, in all metrics including the impact of influencer collaborations on e-commerce sales and brand recognition, making data-driven adjustments to optimize program effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Administrative&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create accurate quotations, and invoices for marketing team products/services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor outstanding debts and follow up with clients for timely payments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in payment collection and send payment reminders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize legal documents (e.g., vendor agreements, NDAs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a filing system for physical and digital records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Marketing, Communications, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 2 years of experience in Influencer Marketing or KOL Management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of influencer marketing, KOL engagement, and social media trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Creative mindset to develop engaging and compelling video content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and coordination skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to analyze data and generate performance reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Proficiency in Microsoft Office, Google Sheets, and Google Slides.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creative and adaptable mindset with a flexible approach to work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail-oriented and well-organized in managing multiple projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Passionate about skincare and beauty trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join a growing team at the forefront of AI development and adoption in ecommerce. You will be responsible for identifying and developing business opportunities, driving adoption of our AI-powered ecommerce platform, and managing client relationships through a consultative, outcomes-focused approach. At its core, this role is about understanding how businesses use data to make decisions — and translating complex workflows into AI capabilities and into clear business value that gives clients a measurable competitive edge&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead end-to-end sales initiatives, including prospecting, qualification, negotiation, and deal closing to consistently achieve and exceed sales targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage prospective clients through impactful presentations, strategic networking, and proactive outreach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present AI-driven solutions and proof of concepts to non-technical stakeholders, translating technical capabilities into compelling business value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong long-term client relationships, ensuring high satisfaction and retention throughout the adoption journey&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare tailored proposals and solution recommendations aligned to specific client needs and business objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with product and technical teams to ensure solutions are positioned accurately and delivered successfully — from initial pitch through to adoption at scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of proven success in AI product management, data/AI technical pre-sales, or solutions consulting with a track record of closing deals preferably within SaaS, AI, ecommerce, or data analytics sectors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to convey complex AI and data concepts clearly and compellingly to diverse audiences — from Marketing Directors and E-commerce VPs to CEOs and technical leads such as CTOs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in consultative selling, including prospecting, qualification, negotiation, and closing — with the ability to position AI solutions against specific client pain points&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with the ecommerce technology landscape and how AI can be applied across them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sufficient understanding of AI concepts such as agents, RAG pipelines, LLMs, and API integrations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable moving fast, learning new AI capabilities as they emerge, and doing what it takes to support a compelling pitch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work effectively across cross-functional teams, acting as the bridge between client needs and technical delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Business, Marketing, Technology, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in English.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Job Responsibilities in a nutshell:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop strategies for the deployment and use of AI within the company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track the use of AI for personal productivity and use it to evangelize to others inside and outside of the company, showing that we use AI effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work to establish policy for the safe use of AI for developers and citizen developers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish lightweight processes to evaluate new AI tools coming into the company for suitability of purpose and corporate standards, including security standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with other product managers to embed AI features into existing and new products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop training programs for staff on effective and safe usage of AI tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Capabilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Essential Qualifications&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Business, Technology, or related field&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Minimum 4 years of experience operating as a product manager, technical evangelist, or in a similar strategic technology role.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Demonstrated ability to advocate for new technologies and drive organizational change and adoption.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Strong communication and presentation skills to effectively evangelize AI usage both internally to staff and externally to clients/partners.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Experience in developing cross-functional policies and training programs&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Proven experience in researching new technologies and techniques for applying technology&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Experience in engaging with Senior Management to gain consensus and sponsorship for key initiatives&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;As this role is regional in nature, strong command of written and spoken English is required. Good command of the Thai language is a strong plus.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Technical &amp;amp; Industry Knowledge&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Deep understanding of current AI tools, generative AI technologies, agent systems, and emerging ecosystem trends.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Knowledge of data privacy, security standards, and ethical considerations surrounding corporate AI deployment.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ability to establish evaluation frameworks and lightweight governance processes for new technology adoption.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Familiarity with the software development lifecycle to effectively collaborate with developers and technical product managers.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;FYwKg fB92N_0&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&quot;FYwKg C6ZIU_0 _3nVJR_0 _2VCbC_0 _2DNlq_0 _1VMf3_0&quot;&gt;Job Description&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;FYwKg fB92N_0&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;vDEj0_0&quot; data-automation=&quot;jobDescription&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;FYwKg&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At aCommerce, the Associate Category Head is a role carved out to meet the changing consumer demand. This individual aims to serve as an extension of our clients’ businesses ensuring proper management and execution of the ecommerce strategy in social commerce on their behalf. This would include developing, managing and executing promotional and marketing campaigns and overall fulfillment execution, smooth day to day operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Associate Category Head, you will be the key lead of our FMCG category. Managing team to develop their category, channel, operation knowledge to deliver aCommerce and Clients revenue, driving business growth, develop relationship with all internal and external parties, including initiative new business growth engine is key contribution to team.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The ideal candidate will be a key business driver with an excellent understanding of online and offline business concepts, practices and procedures. Entrepreneurship, leadership, problem solving, and initiative thinking are necessary. The role will require a combination of strong leadership, financial, business development, account management, and team management skills. This role will build team talent and develop them to be strong future leader.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance Management&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage overall account profitability via P&amp;amp;L management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all clients and channels are successfully on-boarded on time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage to maximize GMV with day-to-day collaboration with client and channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer budget management and P&amp;amp;L execution including reimbursement to deliver agreed GMV, Take Rate, and Profit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring optimal product presentation and visibility on online channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinating with internal cross function and external parties&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and monitor progress against key performance indicators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advising and executing end-to-end social commerce strategy for International brand owners (such as Global brands, FMCG brands etc.). This will include content, sales monitoring, analysis on how to grow demand, supply management and promotion management as well as business analytics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinating with internal departments (tech, warehouse, marketing) and external parties (ad agencies) to troubleshoot and resolve business issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Brand management team to ensure smooth day to day operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong rapport with clients that include managing relationships with internal and external stakeholder&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner Service&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for client relationship and retain client satisfaction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the “face of aCommerce” and primary point of contact for client executives and key stakeholders at each assigned account&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advising clients on how to increase online sales through merchandising, promotion planning and onsite marketing activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing fast-growing e-commerce sales of large brand owners through their own web-store or other online channels and initiative channel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring that regular reviews are carried out with customers, to ensure that their needs are being met and that excellent customer service is achieved and, developing future improvements/services for

&lt;h3&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Program Management &amp;amp; Delivery&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, plan, and manage end-to-end learning programs across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Align academy initiatives with business goals and workforce development needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate program logistics, including scheduling, enrollment, communications, and delivery support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage program calendars and ensure timely execution of cohorts, workshops, and training sessions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Curriculum &amp;amp; Content Development&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the development of comprehensive learning curricula for multiple tracks (e.g., departmental curriculum, functional upskilling, leadership etc).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with subject matter experts (SMEs) to design content that is relevant, engaging, and aligned with desired learning outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop or oversee the creation of learning materials including presentations, eLearning modules, handbooks, facilitator guides, and assessments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure content is adaptable for different learning styles and delivery formats (in-person, online, hybrid).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Stakeholder &amp;amp; Team Collaboration&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with internal teams to identify training needs and learning priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Department Heads to audit and ensure quality of learning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and coach facilitators and trainers to deliver high-impact learning experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;AI &amp;amp; Digital Capability Programs&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the design and rollout of company-wide AI awareness and capability-building programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Technology and business stakeholders to translate AI concepts into practical employee learning experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage AI learning initiatives across the group.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously identify opportunities to improve learning delivery through AI-enabled tools and platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Quality, Measurement &amp;amp; Improvement&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track program engagement, completion, and performance metrics to evaluate effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze learner feedback and performance data to refine curriculum and delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain program documentation, standards, and best practices for scale and sustainability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current on instructional design trends, adult learning principles, and digital learning innovations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Education, Learning &amp;amp; Development or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience in learning program management, curriculum development, or corporate training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to design, develop, and implement scalable learning programs and content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of instructional design models and adult learning principles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in learning platforms, LMS, content authoring and Google suite tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication, stakeholder management, and facilitation skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized with a balance of creativity and execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in both Thai &amp;amp; English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Knowledge in automated script in excel is a plus&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you have what it takes to be part of the aTEAM?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;aCommerce is currently looking for a-class individuals who can enable brands to become high-performing businesses. Our goal is to help brands achieve optimum performance and reach their targets!&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;If you are someone passionate about e-commerce -- an individual with the right skills, passion and commitment to bring brands to the next level, then you might just be the person we are looking for. Join the aTEAM as an Associate Key Account Manager!&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Associate Key Account Manager, you will be the client&#39;s main POC leading the end-to-end process, which includes cross-functional activities involving both internal and external stakeholders. You will also be responsible on developing strong relationships with brands, marketplaces and other channels to drive business growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specifically, this role will be:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing fast-growing e-commerce sales of large brands (such as Nestlé, L&#39;Oréal, Ray-Ban, AIS, etc.) through online marketplaces (Shopee, Lazada, Zalora, 11 Street, LINE, etc.) and their own webstores&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designing and implementing high impact promotion campaigns to increase clients&#39; sales&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring optimal product presentation and visibility on all online channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advising clients on their Ecommerce strategy, in relation to merchandising, promotion planning and marketing activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinating with internal (tech, warehouse, marketing) and external parties (marketplaces)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Potential to evolve to category role with management responsibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Profile:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ideal candidate should be agile with high drive for results, strong inter-personal skills and is strategic. The role will also require a combination of financial acumen, business development and account management skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ year working experience in e-commerce or International Brands (Marketing, commercial/account management roles)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently with high level of responsibilities, including direct relation with clients&#39; persons-in-charge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good knowledge of Excel, PowerPoint and ability to quickly adapt to new software and tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a fast-moving environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fresh graduates are welcome!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;--&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About aCommerce&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;aCommerce is the leading e-commerce enabler and e-distributor in Southeast Asia, delivering retail solutions for global brands such as L’Oreal and Unilever.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Founded in May 2013, aCommerce has over 1,000 staff across offices and fulfilment centres in Singapore, Thailand, Malaysia, Indonesia and the Philippines.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The company is committed to equal opportunities for all of employees and to a work environment free of discrimination and harassment. All employment decisions at aCommerce are based on business needs, job requirements and individual qualifications, without regard to race, religion or belief, gender, sexuality, age, family or parental status, or any other status that may be protected by the laws or regulations in the locations where we operate. We do not tolerate discrimination or harassment based on any of these characteristics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The aTeam is made up of highly ambitious individuals driven to innovate, build and succeed and is always looking for like-minded self-starters to join.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ROLE PURPOSE AND DESCRIPTION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table style=&quot;width: 1195px;&quot; width=&quot;629&quot;&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;width: 417.292px;&quot; width=&quot;136&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;width: 748.125px;&quot; width=&quot;493&quot;&gt;
